nt%20Donald%20Trump.%3Cp%3EMANDEL%20NGAN%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESpecial%20counsel%20Jack%20Smith%20filed%20a%20revised%20election%20interference%20indictment%20against%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20new%20indictment%20removes%20some%20of%20Trump's%20alleged%20conduct%20that%20risked%20presidential%20immunity%20challenges.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20still%20faces%20the%20same%20four%20charges%20that%20were%20in%20the%20first%20indictment%20against%20him.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFormer%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20was%20hit%20with%20a%20revised%20election%20interference%20indictment%20on%20Tuesday%20that%20keeps%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-january-6-criminal-indictment-charges-explained-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20same%20four%20counts%20against%20him%3C%2Fa%3E%20but%20removes%20some%20of%20the%20alleged%20conduct%20that%20may%20now%20be%20protected%20by%20presidential%20immunity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20office%20of%20special%20counsel%20Jack%20Smith%20announced%20the%20new%2C%20superseding%20indictment%20shortly%20after%20a%20second%20grand%20jury%20voted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BToday%2C%20a%20federal%20grand%20jury%20in%20the%20District%20of%20Columbia%20returned%20a%20superseding%20indictment%2C%20ECF%20No.%20226%2C%20charging%20the%20defendant%20with%20the%20same%20criminal%20offenses%20that%20were%20charged%20in%20the%20original%20indictment%2C%26quot%3B%20Smith's%20office%20said%20in%20an%20email%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20superseding%20indictment%2C%20which%20was%20presented%20to%20a%20new%20grand%20jury%20that%20had%20not%20previously%20heard%20evidence%20in%20this%20case%2C%20reflects%20the%20Government's%20efforts%20to%20respect%20and%20implement%20the%20Supreme%20Court's%20holdings%20and%20remand%20instructions%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20statement%20continued.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETrump%20remains%20charged%20with%20the%20same%20four%20counts%20of%20interfering%20with%20the%202020%20election.%20Those%20counts%20allege%20that%20he%20conspired%20to%20defraud%20the%20United%20States%2C%20that%20he%20conspired%20to%20obstruct%20the%20certification%20of%20the%20electoral%20vote%20count%2C%20that%20he%20did%20obstruct%20that%20certification%2C%20and%20that%20he%20conspired%20to%20deprive%20voters%20of%20the%20right%20to%20have%20their%20votes%20counted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20re-tooled%20indictment%20is%20a%20response%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-trump-immunity-january-6-election-ruling-decision-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Supreme%20Court's%20landmark%20opinion%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20last%20month%20that%20provides%20presidents%20with%20broad%20protection%20from%20being%20prosecuted%20for%20official%20acts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20removes%2C%20for%20example%2C%20any%20reference%20from%20the%20first%20indictment%20that%20alleges%20he%20conferred%20with%20Justice%20Department%20officials%20in%20promoting%20false%20claims%20of%20election%20fraud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20indictment%20is%2036%20pages%20long%3B%20the%20previous%20indictment%20was%2045%20pages%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESenior%20Assistant%20Special%20Counsel%20Molly%20Gaston%20said%20in%20a%20separate%20filing%20Tuesday%20that%20Smith's%20office%20is%20not%20asking%20that%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ETrump%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%20appear%20in%20court%20to%20be%20arraigned%20on%20the%20new%20indictment.%20He%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20to%20the%20previous%20indictment.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20a%20developing%20story.%20Please%20check%20back%20for%20updates.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-hit-with-revised-january-6-indictment-jack-smith-2024-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22publishe