s%20and%20is%20delicate.%3Cp%3EMississippi%20Department%20of%20Environmental%20Quality%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tusk%20weighs%20a%20couple%20hundred%20pounds%2C%20so%20Templeton%20was%20going%20to%20need%20some%20help%20moving%20it.%20That's%20why%20he%20contacted%20Starnes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20about%208%3A30%20in%20the%20morning%20when%20Starnes%20got%20the%20text.%20He%20and%20his%20colleagues%20are%20used%20to%20dealing%20with%20what%20he%20calls%20fossil%20emergencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20spouses%20know%20that%20we%20can%20get%20called%20on%20any%20minute%20to%20go%20grab%20one%20of%20these%20things%2C%26quot%3B%20Starnes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20important%20to%20move%20the%20tusk%20quickly%20so%20it%20didn't%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscientists-revive-mammoth-dodo-colossal-biosciences-2023-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estart%20to%20deteriorate%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20help%20preserve%20and%20transport%20the%20tusk%20with%20minimal%20damage%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EStarnes%2C%20Templeton%2C%20and%20Jonathan%20Leard%2C%20another%20MDEQ%20employee%2C%20covered%20it%20in%20foil%20and%20made%20a%20jacket%20of%20burlap%20and%20plaster.%20With%20the%20plaster%20cover%2C%20it%20weighed%20600%20pounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20was%20a%2050-foot%20bluff%20they%20had%20to%20haul%20it%20up%20to%20get%20to%20a%20truck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20an%20all-day%20affair%2C%26quot%3B%20Starnes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EExperts%20can%20learn%20a%20lot%20from%20the%20tusk.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20person%20in%20an%20orange%20shirt%20and%20sun%20hat%20covers%20a%20mammoth%20tusk%20in%20plaster%20and%20foil%20on%20a%20creek%20bank%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cd0ed843b5e59d16b572d9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EExperts%20protected%20the%20tusk%20with%20plaster%20before%20moving%20it.%3Cp%3EMississippi%20Department%20of%20Environmental%20Quality%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETempleton's%20discovery%20is%20exciting%20for%20a%20couple%20of%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20it's%20rare%20%E2%80%94%20%26quot%3Bwe%20don't%20really%20have%20a%20whole%20lot%20of%20these%20animals%20represented%20in%20our%20fossil%20record%2C%26quot%3B%20Starnes%20said.%20And%20second%2C%20it's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmummified-frozen-wolf-may-have-ancient-pleistocene-viruses-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enearly%20complete%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20including%20the%20tusk's%20tip.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20it%20was%20a%20tusk%20is%20also%20great%20news%20for%20experts%20because%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Etusks%20contain%20a%20lot%20more%20information%20about%20a%20mammoth%20than%2C%20say%2C%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ea%20leg%20bone.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20can%20tell%20about%20this%20whole%20animal's%20life%20by%20studying%20the%20tusk%2C%26quot%3B%20Starnes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMammoths%20accumulated%20layers%20to%20their%20tusks%20each%20year%20similar%20to%20tree%20rings%2C%20preserving%20a%20record%20of%20where%20they%20were%20and%20whether%20there%20was%20enough%20to%20eat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffires-may-have-caused-la-brea-tar-pit-extinctions-thousands-of-years-ago-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etusk's%20examination%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20still%20in%20its%20early%20days%2C%20previous%20research%20on%20other%20mammoth%20tusks%20shows%20just%20how%20much%20Starnes%20and%20his%20colleagues%20can%20learn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20scientists%20published%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fsciadv.adk0818%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%3C%2Fa%3E%20tracing%20a%2014%2C000-year-old%20woolly%20mammoth's%20movements%20through%20Canada%20and%20Alaska%20based%20on%20an%20analysis%20of%20just%20her%20tusk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tusk%20will%20hopefully%20be%20ready%20to%20show%20at%20the%20Mississippi%20Museum%20of%20Natural%20Science's%20fossil%20roadshow%20in%20March%2C%20Starnes%20said.%20Though%2C%20it'll%20need%20some%20repair%20beforehand%20since%20it%20cracked%20during%20transport.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20rest%20of%20the%20mammoth%20could%20still%20be%20in%20the%20river.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20bank%20of%20a%20creek%20in%20Mississippi%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cd0f281aa2ac29ee347832%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EEddie%20Templeton%20knows%20how%20to%20keep%20a%20lookout%20for%20fossils%20in%20creeks.%3Cp%3EMississippi%20Department%20of%20Environmental%20Quality%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20tusk%20is%20just%20part%20of%20a%20bigger%20story.%20For%20instance%2C%20the%20layers%20of%20sediment%20around%20it%20give%20Starnes%20some%20clues%20about%20how%20the%20fossil%20got%20to%20the%20creek%20bank%20in%20the%20first%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20do%20know%20by%20studying%20the%20geology%20around%20it%20exactly%20what%20happened%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20tells%20us%20a%20really%2C%20really%20detailed%20story.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20the%20mammoth%20probably%20came%20to%20the%20creek%20and%20died%20before%20its%20carcass%20was%20washed%20away%20and%20buried%2C%20with%20the%20tusk%20detached.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20not%20uncommon%20for%20tusks%20to%20separate%20from%20the%20rest%20of%20a%20mammoth%20skeleton.%20Even%20with%20well-preserved%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcanada-near-perfect-baby-mammoth-found-in-yukons-klondike-gold-fields-2022-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efrozen%20specimens%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20tusks%20tend%20to%20fall%20off%20as%20they%20thaw%2C%20Starnes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20another%20lucky%20fossil%20hunter%20will%20come%20across%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20skeleton%20one%20day.%20%26quot%3BChances%20are%20somewhere%20in%20that%20alluvium%20of%20that%20stream%2C%20the%20rest%20of%20it's%20in%20there%2C%20probably%20not%20nearby%2C%26quot%3B%20Starnes%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ETempleton%20has%20tips%20for%20other%20fossil%20hunters.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20covers%20a%20mammoth%20tusk%20in%20plaster%20on%20a%20creek%20bank%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66cd0f901aa2ac29ee347837%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EExperts%20hope%20the%20tusk%20will%20eventually%20go%20on%20permanent%20display.%3Cp%3EMississippi%20Department%20of%20Environmental%20Quality%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETempleton%20has%20been%20fossil%20hunting%20for%20decades%20and%20has%20adopted%20a%20few%20tips%20along%20the%20way.%20Templeton's%20first%20tip%20is%20to%20just%20be%20aware%20of%20the%20types%20of%20fossils%20that%20you're%20likely%20to%20find%20in%20your%20area.%20Many%20of%20his%20finds%20come%20from%20creeks'%20gravel%20beds.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20good%20for%20people%20to%20realize%20those%20sorts%20of%20things%20are%20out%20there%20and%20just%20be%20paying%20attention%20because%20anybody%20could%20have%20walked%20up%20on%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20Templeton%20said%20of%20the%20tusk.%20%26quot%3BI%20didn't%20do%20anything%20special.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETempleton%20said%20it's%20also%20important%20to%20share%20what%20you%20find%20with%20experts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStarnes%20said%20he%20and%20his%20colleagues%20don't%20get%20as%20much%20time%20for%20fieldwork%2C%20so%20they%20rely%20on%20amateur%20fossil%20hunters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20stuff%20that%20is%20foun